# Network: Destinations 10.0.0.1-.2-.3 are physical micro-links traversed
# inside topology. Source port 2000 marks start and 2001 marks completion.
# Policy: Only start-phase packets pass unchanged; completed packets cannot re-enter.
# Topology: Address transitions iterate internally, then destination .3 changes the phase port.
# Property multi-link-one-hop: Destination .1 reaches .3/completed within one topology evaluation.
# Property second-suffix: Destination .2 needs one internal topology step.
# Property third-zero-link: Destination .3 uses zero star iterations before completion.
# Property intermediate-not-exposed: The topology expression must finish, not expose .2/start.
# Property completed-cannot-restart: A completed packet at .1 is rejected by policy.
policy = filter(src_port = 2000);
topology =
  (((filter(dst_ip = 10.0.0.1) . dst_ip <- 10.0.0.2)
    + (filter(dst_ip = 10.0.0.2) . dst_ip <- 10.0.0.3))*
   . filter(dst_ip = 10.0.0.3)
   . src_port <- 2001);
check multi-link-one-hop: dst_ip = 10.0.0.1 & src_port = 2000 => dst_ip = 10.0.0.3 & src_port = 2001;
check second-suffix: dst_ip = 10.0.0.2 & src_port = 2000 => dst_ip = 10.0.0.3 & src_port = 2001;
check third-zero-link: dst_ip = 10.0.0.3 & src_port = 2000 => dst_ip = 10.0.0.3 & src_port = 2001;
check intermediate-not-exposed: dst_ip = 10.0.0.1 & src_port = 2000 => dst_ip = 10.0.0.2 & src_port = 2000;
check completed-cannot-restart: dst_ip = 10.0.0.1 & src_port = 2001 => dst_ip = 10.0.0.3;
